    "description": "Are you an expert in Windows internals with a passion for low-level software engineering? At Ivanti, you'll have the opportunity to develop and maintain critical Windows applications, services, and device drivers used by organizations worldwide to manage and secure their digital environments. As a vital member of our Secure Unified Endpoint Management team, you'll shape both on-premises and SaaS solutions, ensuring seamless performance and security across all deployment landscapes.\n\nWhy this role matters\nIvanti is seeking a highly skilled Windows low-level software engineer who excels in Windows internals to develop and maintain Windows applications, services and has some Windows device driver development experience to work across multiple security products within the Secure Unified Endpoint Management portfolio. This engineer will be working both with on-premises product offerings as well as SaaS cloud products as these key components are shared across these different deployment environments.\n\nWhat you'll do:\nâ¢ Manage Windows logo and certification pipelines (WHQL, SVVP, etc.) to ensure seamless installation, reliable operation, and ongoing compliance with industry standards.\nâ¢ Build robust Windows applications, services, and device drivers using the Windows SDK & DDK, while establishing frameworks for service and driver stability across multiple Ivanti products.\nâ¢ Design modernization strategies to adopt the latest Windows APIs, frameworks, and driver models for enhanced functionality and future-proofing of Ivanti's offerings.\nâ¢ Partner with Product Managers and Technical Support to address technical issues, triage incompatibilities, and collaboratively define future features based on broad customer needs.\nâ¢ Lead porting efforts to new hardware platforms, such as Windows on ARM, ensuring broad support for plugin hardware devices, networking, and PC platforms within product lines.\nâ¢ Collaborate with cross-functional teams to optimize and enhance existing driversâespecially in storage and networkingâfor improved performance and reliability across platforms.\nâ¢ Advise stakeholders on best practices for continuous delivery and quality assurance, promoting innovative solutions to maintain high standards of service and driver stability.\n\nWhat you will bring:\nâ¢ Bachelor's degree in computer science or related engineering field\nâ¢ 5+ years of Microsoft Windows software development experience using the Windows SDK for applications and Windows services.\nâ¢ 2+ years of experience with Windows device driver development (including kernel-mode, and Windows Driver Model Drivers, Windows Driver Kit)\nâ¢ Experience developing Windows applications & services\nâ¢ Strong expertise in Windows Internals such as memory management, interrupt handling, I/O mechanisms, kernel/user mode boundaries, and multi-threading programming.\nâ¢ Kernel-level debugging skills (live systems and using crash dump analysis using debug/PDB files, WinDbg, Static Driver Verified and other related tools)\nâ¢ Strong team player with excellent communication skills<br/><br/>Please mention the word **TERRIFICALLY** and tag RMTAxLjQyLjk5LjEyMg== when applying to show you read the job post completely (#RMTAxLjQyLjk5LjEyMg==). This is a beta feature to avoid spam applicants. Companies can search these words to find applicants that read this and see they're human.",
